en_626452_0	President Maithripala Sirisena has received blessings paying obeisance to the historic Kirivehera.
en_626452_1	President Maithripala Sirisena visited to historic Kataragama Sacred site in view of his birthday and engaged in religious observances.
en_626452_2	The President also paid obeisance to the Kirivehera.
en_626452_3	Members of the Maha Sangha including the Ven.
en_626452_4	Thalagala Gnanendra Thera of Kirivehera showered blessings on the President.
en_626452_5	The President also participated in an Ashirvadha Pooja conducted at the Kataragama Maha Devale.
en_626452_6	President Maithripala Sirisena also received blessings visiting the other Devales in the premises.
en_626452_7	Among those who joined in the occasion was a group including the Basnayake Nilame of the Ruhunu Kataragama Maha Devale Dilruwan Rajapaksa.
en_626452_8	Meanwhile, an Ashirvada Bodhi Pooja organized by the North Central Governor’s Office in view of the President’s birthday was held near the Jaya Sri Mahabodhi.
en_626452_9	The Pinkama was organized under the guidance of the Chief Incumbent of the Atamasthana the Ven.
en_626452_10	Dr. Pallegama Sirinivasa Thera.
